Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.00,0:00:26.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs100\t(,\fs110)\frz1\fad(3000,500)\fsp0\fscx120\pos(960,800)\b0\shad0\bord0}地          球          脉          动
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.34,0:00:31.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,远离一切陆地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Away from all land
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.90,0:00:34.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海洋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.74,0:00:38.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球表面多半被海洋覆盖着\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It covers more than half the surface of our planet
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.94,0:00:43.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,至今海洋的许多地方我们还无法触及\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and yet for the most part it is beyond our reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.18,0:00:49.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,许多地方实际上很荒凉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Much of it is virtually empty
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.14,0:00:52.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水之荒漠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a watery desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.54,0:01:04.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里的生命被迫不停寻找食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}All life that is here is locked in a constant search to find food
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.10,0:01:11.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这广袤的大洋中只为获得宝贵的能量\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a struggle to conserve precious energy in the open ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.00,0:01:18.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs150\fsp5.5\fad(1000,1000)\pos(965,900)\bord0\shad0}无     垠     深     海
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.00,0:01:26.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs60\fsp5\fad(1000,1000)\pos(960,1080)\bord0\shad3}画 外 音\N{\fs90}大卫 · 爱登堡   爵士
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.22,0:01:33.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是最大的鱼类\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The biggest of all fish
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.30,0:01:37.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,30吨重,12米长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}thirty tons in weight, twelve meters long
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.82,0:01:40.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鲸鲨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a whale shark.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.18,0:01:47.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的巨大身躯上是靠吃一种很小的海洋生物长成的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's huge bulk is sustained by mere microscopic creatures of the sea
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.94,0:01:49.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,浮游生物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Plankton.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.38,0:01:59.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鲸鲨经常在它的最好的进食地点之间洄游\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Whale sharks cruise on regular habitual routes between the best feeding grounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.46,0:02:09.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,二月,鲸鲨从遥远的委内瑞拉海岸来到这片浅海\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In February, that takes them to the surface waters far from the coast of Venezuela.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.06,0:02:15.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里已经有访客了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Others are already here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.18,0:02:20.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,饵鱼(当饵料的鱼)因为同一原因来到这里 吃浮游生物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Baitfish have come for the same reason to feed on the plankton.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.38,0:02:25.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鲸鲨非常准时地到场\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The whale shark has timed it's arrival exactly right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.62,0:02:31.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,奇怪的是,小鱼围着鲸鲨游\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Oddly, the tiny fish swarm around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.18,0:02:41.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小鱼利用鲸鲨当盾牌\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're using it as a shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.46,0:02:48.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有掠食性鱼类在附近潜伏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Other predatory fish are lurking nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.14,0:02:56.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黄鳍金枪鱼(黄鳍鲔) 看上去比鲸鲨机灵多了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Yellowfin tuna. They seem wary of the giant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.30,0:03:07.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鲸鲨开始下潜,离开这过度拥挤的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The shark dives, as if to escape from such overcrowding.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.78,0:03:17.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在黄鳍金枪鱼开始进攻这没有保护的饵鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now the tuna have a chance to attack the unprotected baitfish
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.38,0:03:32.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而后,鲸鲨归来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but then back comes the giant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.86,0:03:42.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鲸鲨张开大口,满嘴都是饵鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It has taken a vast mouthful of the baitfish itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.58,0:03:49.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,浮游生物看来并不是鲸鲨的唯一食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Plankton, it seems, is not the only food for a whale shark.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.30,0:04:02.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鲸鲨和金枪鱼一起享受这大餐\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Both shark and tuna feast together
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.94,0:04:20.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,金枪鱼必须机警地远离鲸鲨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the tuna must be wary.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.22,0:04:27.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,除非它们想成为鲸鲨的腹中美餐\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Even they can end up in the whale shark's stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.30,0:04:40.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,掠食者在这里想怎么吃就怎么吃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Predators here must grab what they can, when they can
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.86,0:04:44.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为好事不多,好景不长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for such events do not last long.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.54,0:04:52.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有在水况非常好的情况下 才会出现这样的鱼群聚集\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The dense shoals, on which so many depend gather only when water conditions are perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.54,0:05:11.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,许多掠食者把大部分的时间用在来回巡游\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Many predators spend much of their time cruising the open ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.14,0:05:12.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,寻找食物上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}endlessly searching.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.94,0:05:20.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,吃浮游生物的蝠鲼也是\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Plankton feeding rays do so,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.38,0:05:22.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用最省力的方式在水中滑翔\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}gliding with minimum effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.30,0:05:40.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,远洋白鳍鲨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The oceanic whitetip shark
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.46,0:05:45.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也是节省能量的旅行者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}another energy efficient traveler.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.70,0:05:53.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它擅长的是即使在最空荡的海域也能找到猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It specializes in locating prey in the emptiest areas of the open ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.18,0:05:56.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巡游高度在海平面至水下100米之间\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}patrolling the top one hundred meters of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.06,0:06:09.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鲨鱼能在水中“闻”到各种气味\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Taste in water, is the equivalent of smell in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.94,0:06:14.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,白鳍鲨更是能跟踪细微的痕迹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}An oceanic whitetip is able to detect even the faintest trace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.66,0:06:20.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小小的引水鱼跟着它游\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Small pilot fish swim with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.14,0:06:24.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鲨鱼比它们更容易发现猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The shark can find prey far more easily than they can
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.46,0:06:27.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引水鱼就收集鲨鱼咬碎的食物碎片吃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they'll be able to collect the scraps from it's meals.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.98,0:06:36.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的长长的垂直的胸鳍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's long, fixed pectoral fins
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.14,0:06:41.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以让它花费很小的力量在水里巡游\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}enable it to soar through the water, with the least expenditure of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.42,0:06:50.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鲨鱼发现了一群香蕉鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This shark has found a school of rainbow runners.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.26,0:06:53.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这给了鲨鱼一个机会\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It would eat one, given the chance
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.98,0:06:57.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是香蕉鱼游的敏捷迅速,白鳍鲨不容易捉到\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but rainbow runners are swift and agile and not easily caught
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.34,0:07:03.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此鲨鱼耐心等候\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so, it bides it's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.10,0:07:09.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能到最后可以找到一条 容易抓到的老弱的鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There's a chance that, eventually, it may spot a weakened fish that's catchable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.46,0:07:16.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,猎人,还在无尽的等待着\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The hunter
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.54,0:07:30.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使远离陆地也有刺激的事情\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}endlessly waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.06,0:07:42.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一群多达500条的真海豚\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Excitement far from land.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.94,0:08:00.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们感觉到附近有食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A school of dolphin five hundred strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.34,0:08:02.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开始加速追赶\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They've sensed there's food around, and they're racing to catch up with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.70,0:08:14.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,消息传开,大量的真海豚上路了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The news has spread. Now a number of schools are on their way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.86,0:08:34.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们向亚速尔游去 葡萄牙以西1000英里的火山群岛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're heading towards the Azores volcanic islands a thousand miles west of Portugal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.90,0:08:49.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海豚利用声纳扫描大海\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The dolphin scan the water ahead with their sonar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.26,0:08:51.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,已经接近目标\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're close to their target.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.66,0:09:04.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是了!竹荚鲭\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is it. Scad mackerel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.26,0:09:09.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,单只海豚想吃它们是很困难的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's difficult for a single dolphin to catch the fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.54,0:09:14.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了避免浪费精力,它们进行团队合作\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To avoid wasting energy the work as a group.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.98,0:09:26.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们将鱼儿赶上海面,目的是诱捕它们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They drive the fish upwards, trapping them against the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.42,0:09:31.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为那里还有掠食者在等着鱼儿们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and there, other predators await them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.94,0:09:42.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,猛鹱 正在等着海豚把猎物赶上水面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Cory's shearwaters. They're waiting for the dolphin to drive the prey closer to the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.26,0:09:57.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,猛鹱出动了 它们可以潜至20米甚至更深来捉鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now the shearwaters can dive down on them, descending to twenty meters or more
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.46,0:10:05.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海豚们锁定了从海面撤退的鱼群\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the dolphins block the baitball's retreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.02,0:10:39.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海豚吃饱后迅速离开了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The dolphins leave as soon as they've had their fill
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.62,0:10:49.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最后,竹荚鲭也逃出了猛鹱的攻击范围.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and, at last, the mackerel sink below the diving range of the birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.14,0:11:19.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,昼去夜至,海洋发生了另一个重大变化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the Sun disappears, a profound change takes place in the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.98,0:11:27.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,深海的浮游生物开始浮上水面, 另一支饥饿的部队准备接受这些猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Deep water plankton start to rise from the depths and another hungry army prepares to receive it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.90,0:11:55.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果环境适宜\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Every night, wherever conditions are right,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.25,0:12:01.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每天晚上会有无数的深海生物到海面来觅食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}countless millions of creatures from the deep migrate to the surface, seeking food.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.46,0:12:12.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一条小旗鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A baby sailfish,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.22,0:12:16.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仅15厘米长.边游边大快朵颐\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}fifteen centimeters long, snaps up everything in it's path.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.42,0:12:24.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再过3年,它将重达60公斤 成为海洋中强大的猎手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In three years' time, it'll be one of the oceans most formidable hunters weighing sixty kilos.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.26,0:12:28.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只是现在很弱小罢了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Just now, however, it's very vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.74,0:13:13.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种蝠鲼非常巨大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These manta rays are giants.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.70,0:13:17.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,8米宽,超过2吨重\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Eight meters across and weighing over two tons.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.02,0:13:27.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,头部对称的2块刀片状的凸状物 帮助蝠鲼把浮游生物送到嘴里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The blade-like projections on either side of the head help to steer plankton into the manta's mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.98,0:13:51.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黎明到来,浮游生物又回到深海\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Dawn returns, and the plankton sinks back into the depths.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.06,0:13:57.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果想要跟下去,必须乘潜水艇\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}If we are to follow, we must use a submarine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.38,0:14:03.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着我们在黑暗中不断下潜\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As we descend into the darkness,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.10,0:14:07.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水压越来越大,温度越来越低\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the pressure builds, the temperature falls.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.50,0:14:15.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在500米深处,新的神秘动物出现了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Below five hundred meters, new, mysterious animals appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.62,0:14:27.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们奇异的外形帮助它们在漆黑的空间里悬浮\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their bizarre shapes help them to remain suspended in the dark space.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.98,0:14:35.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有一些貌似浅海生物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some resemble creatures familiar from shallower waters
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.50,0:14:46.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另一些则长相怪异\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}others defy classification.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.14,0:14:56.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,周围全都是飘下来的有机颗粒\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}All around, organic particles drift downwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.66,0:15:04.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海雪是海洋表面上的生物产生的小型有机物碎屑\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Marine snow, detritus from the creatures swarming in the sunlit waters above.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.06,0:15:12.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这场“雪”给这里的许多动物提供了食物, 比如这只蜘蛛蟹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The snow is food for many animals here, like the sea spider
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.46,0:15:15.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与虾和螃蟹有一定的亲戚关系\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a small relative of shrimps and crabs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.06,0:15:33.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的这些附肢样的奇怪的腿, 上面的羽毛可以防止它沉下去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Those strange leg-like appendages are feathered, to stop it from sinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.70,0:15:38.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的腿也可以接住海雪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They can also enmesh marine snow
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.06,0:15:42.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后将挑选过的食物送进嘴里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}which it wipes carefully into it's jaws.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.90,0:16:02.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一条锯齿鳗笔直向上, 静静地挂在水里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A sawtooth eel hangs upright and motionless.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.54,0:16:13.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,向上凝视, 可让它在微弱光线的环境下发现猎物的影像\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Gazing ever upwards, it watches for prey, silhouetted against the faint glimmerings of light from the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.74,0:16:25.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它可以在这里挂好几天. 直到猎物近到让它可以发动攻击\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Days may pass before prey swims close enough for it to strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.26,0:16:34.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着下潜深度增加,周围已经一片漆黑\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Farther down still, the blackness is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.18,0:16:39.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有阳光可以照射到这么深\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}No vestige of sunlight can penetrate as far as this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.30,0:16:45.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,食物非常缺乏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Food is very scarce
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.02,0:16:49.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一点能量都不能浪费\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and nothing can afford to waste any energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.82,0:16:55.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小飞象章鱼拍打翅膀来游泳\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A dumbo octopus simply flaps a fin
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.86,0:17:01.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不象它的浅海亲戚利用喷射水流的反作用力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}no need for the jet propulsion used by it's shallow water relatives above.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.14,0:17:35.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个奇异世界中的最神秘生物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The weirdest, in this world of the strange,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.14,0:17:40.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,幽灵蛸,来自地狱的吸血鬼鱿鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}vampyroteuthis, the vampire squid from hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.06,0:17:49.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它受到惊动就会稍稍后撤\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Disturb it and it only retreats a little distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.86,0:17:57.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果继续惊动它,就会看到它的特别防御\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Go after it, and it has a special defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.74,0:18:04.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想看它要做什么,就要关掉灯光\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To see what it does, you must switch off the lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.10,0:18:10.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,吸血鬼鱿鱼可以自行发光\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The vampire squid has lights of it's own.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.42,0:18:19.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的足囊中的发光微生物发出的光可以迷惑敌人\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Bioluminescent bacteria shine from pockets on it's arms to confuse it's predators.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.14,0:18:22.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些是眼吗\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Are those eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.02,0:18:32.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上这些发光的触手末端用来吸引掠食者攻击 从而保护头部不受伤害\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In fact they're spots at the end of it's mantle. A bite there, would leave the head unscathed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.50,0:18:41.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,威胁消失,吸血鬼鱿鱼也消失在黑暗中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The threat diminishes, and vampyroteuthis disappears into the blackness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.78,0:19:00.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终来到海床上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At last, the sea floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.30,0:19:02.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,离海平面2英里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Over two miles down,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.10,0:19:07.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,压强是地面的300倍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the pressure here is three hundred times that at the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.14,0:19:14.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海雪落到这里也要好几个月的时间\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It takes several months for marine snow to drift down as far as this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.18,0:19:25.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当你越过满是岩石的海底陆地边缘 前面便是广阔的海底平原\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As you travel away from the rocky margins of the continents an immense plain stretches ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.54,0:19:31.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,绵延几千英里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It extends for thousands of miles
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.54,0:19:34.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,逐渐向下蔓延\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}gradually sinking downwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.58,0:19:43.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海底泥中也有些微的踪迹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are faint trails in the ooze,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.10,0:19:47.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,证明即使在这里也有生命存在\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}signs that even here there is life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.50,0:19:57.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是其中一种\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are what made some of them
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.74,0:20:02.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海胆,收集并过滤漂流物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}sea urchins sifting the accumulating drifts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.30,0:20:12.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虾用脚尖优雅地站着, 很挑剔的选择最吸引它们的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Shrimps standing on elegant tiptoe fastidiously select the particles that appeal to them
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.22,0:20:28.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过海底也和其他地方一样, 既然有吃素的,肯定有吃肉的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but, in the deep sea, as everywhere else if there are grazers, there are hunters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.10,0:20:42.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一只安康鱼 肉眼几乎不能辨别躺在那里的它和沙子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A monkfish, almost indistinguishable from the sand on which it lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.74,0:20:54.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,既然有引诱猎物过来的诱饵 何必浪费能量到处追赶猎物呢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Why waste energy chasing around, if you can attract prey towards you with a lure?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.30,0:21:14.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个可能有点大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Maybe that one was a bit big.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.82,0:21:21.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,安康鱼可以等好几天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The monkfish can wait, for days if necessary,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.42,0:21:24.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到合适的猎物出现\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}until the right sized meal turns up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.06,0:21:32.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,食腐类动物则需要到处寻找食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Scavengers on the other hand, have to move around to find their food.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.74,0:21:44.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蟹类可以从水里嗅到从上面落下的尸体的极细微的气味 并以此追踪到食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Crabs can detect the faintest of tastes in the water and that helps them locate the latest body to drift down from above.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.66,0:21:48.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鳗鱼已经在这里进食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Eels are already feeding on the corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.58,0:21:59.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等脚类动物,比如1/3米长的巨海虱\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Isopods, like giant marine woodlice a third of a meter long
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.94,0:22:02.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也在撕食腐烂的肉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}are ripping into the rotting flesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.14,0:22:11.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在接下来的几个小时里, 这些食腐动物会尽情分享这份大餐\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Over the next few hours there'll be frenzied competition between scavengers of all kinds to grab a share.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.26,0:22:44.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时候,也有想不到的大好事\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Just occasionally, there is a gigantic bonanza.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.58,0:22:56.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一头抹香鲸的尸体\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The remains of a sperm whale.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.22,0:23:00.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,约5个月前死亡\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It died five months or so ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.22,0:23:04.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,除了粘在骨头上的鲸脂外已经没什么东西了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There's little left but fatty blubber clinging to it's bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.86,0:23:11.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鲸鱼肉滋养了方圆几里的生物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's flesh has nourished life for miles around
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.46,0:23:14.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但现在盛宴快结束了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but now the feast is almost over.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.98,0:23:24.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宽达1米的蜘蛛蟹仍然在采集这最后的残羹剩饭\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Spider crabs, a meter across, still pick at the last putrid remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.58,0:23:37.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再过几个星期,除了骨头外什么都不会留下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A few weeks more, and nothing will be left, but bare bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.50,0:23:43.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蜘蛛蟹必须尽快吃完.直到下一个畜体落下之前\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The crabs will have to fast, until the next carcass drifts down.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.10,0:23:54.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过不是所有的食物来自阳光普照的海面上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But not all food comes from the sunlit world above.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.54,0:24:04.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大西洋被一条无边的火山山脉劈成两半\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The floor of the Atlantic Ocean is split in two by an immense volcanic mountain chain that winds unbroken
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.00,0:24:07.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,绕地球绵延45000英里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for forty five thousand miles around the globe.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.30,0:24:19.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这里 海底裂缝中含有大量溶解矿物质的滚烫海水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In places, it's riven by great fissures, from which superheated water loaded with dissolved minerals
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.34,0:24:22.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喷进冰冷的深海里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}blasts into the icy depths.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.86,0:24:39.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,硫化物冷却所形成的浓烟有3层楼那么高\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Clouds of sulfides solidify into towering chimneys, as tall as a three story house.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.34,0:24:52.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,400度的高温 剧毒的化学物质足可以杀死绝大多数生物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At four hundred degrees this scalding cocktail of chemicals would be lethally toxic to most forms of life
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.94,0:24:58.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是令人震惊的是 一种特别的细菌在这里繁荣昌盛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but astoundingly, a particular kind of bacteria thrives here
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.50,0:25:04.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大量的虾又以细菌为食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and feeding on the bacteria, vast numbers of shrimps.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.22,0:25:20.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使在没有太阳的能量驱动, 也会诞生丰富的共生动物群\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So, beyond the farthest reach of the Sun's power a rich independent community exists,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.38,0:25:25.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并直接吸收从地心喷出的能量\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that draws all it's energy directly from the Earth's molten core.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.62,0:25:45.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在地球的另一端,西太平洋和日本的交界处\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}On the other side of the planet, in the western Pacific bordering Japan
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.66,0:25:48.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,龙火山带\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the dragon chimneys,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.58,0:25:53.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另一些在黑暗的海底喷发的火山口\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}another series of hot vents, erupting in the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.14,0:26:05.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里更多的不同的细菌因为相同的原因而繁荣着\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here, more, but different bacteria thrive in a similar way.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.10,0:26:18.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这里也有很多甲壳类动物 不过和大西洋的海底火山迥然不同\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And here, too, more crustaceans, but quite different species from those around the hot vents in the Atlantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.74,0:26:27.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些螯龙虾(属蟹类)\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are squat lobsters,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.94,0:26:34.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,覆盖着有毛的甲壳, 互相争抢最佳位置\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}clad in furry armor jostling with one another beside the jets of superheated water
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.00,0:26:37.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来摄取喷出的炙热海水中的细菌\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for the best places, from which to graze on bacteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.86,0:26:49.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种和大西洋相似的现象,相当于一个个绿洲\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These vents, too, like those in the Atlantic are isolated oases
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.26,0:26:53.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,分布广泛,又各自独立\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so widely separated, that each community is unique.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.34,0:27:06.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在太平洋的其他地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Cross to the other side of the Pacific,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.86,0:27:13.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,加拉帕戈斯群岛附近的海底, 还有另一个海底裂缝在喷射炙热海水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to the deep near the Galapagos Islands and there are yet other fissures venting superheated water.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.82,0:27:24.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,距海面一英里半,一个叫北九地区的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}One and a half miles down, at a site known as Nine North
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.94,0:27:30.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,高耸的火山烟囱滋养着引人入胜的巨大管栖蠕虫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}towering chimneys support a spectacular display of giant tubeworms.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.62,0:27:42.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些火山口带来的丰富的能源 甚至可以让这些蠕虫长到3米长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These vents give off so much energy that some of the worms reach three meters in length.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.42,0:27:47.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是已知长的最快的海洋无脊椎动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're the fastest growing marine invertebrates known.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.18,0:27:58.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,据统计,超过50种生活在这里的生物被发现\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}All told, over fifty different species have so far been found living here.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.42,0:28:05.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些熙熙攘攘的生物群落\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The inhabitants of these bustling communities
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.38,0:28:10.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,生长速度虽然很快,不过存在的时间也可能很短\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}may grow at speed but their existence can also be short,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.46,0:28:13.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为火山口的喷发是不确定的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for the vents do not erupt indefinitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.18,0:28:18.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,说不定突然间它们就会消失\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Suddenly, unpredictably, they may become inactive.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.90,0:28:26.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,9个月后,北九地区\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Nine months have passed at Nine North.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.66,0:28:34.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火山口丰富的生物群现在 只剩下了寒冷贫瘠荒凉的遗址\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}What were only recently chimneys teeming with life have turned into cold, sterile mineral monuments.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.74,0:28:44.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地壳喷出的能量漩涡转移到了别处\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some eddy, deep in the Earth's crust diverted the volcanic energy elsewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.06,0:28:49.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,整个微观世界也黯然失色\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and, an entire microworld was extinguished.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.74,0:29:02.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在有的地方,火山喷发后会形成巨大的水下山\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In places, volcanoes have erupted to build great submarine mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.70,0:29:07.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,据估计海底共有30000座火山\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are thought to be around thirty thousand such volcanoes
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.34,0:29:13.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果从海床开始算 甚至有一些比珠穆朗玛峰还要高\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}some, measured from the sea floor, are taller than Everest.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.94,0:29:23.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火山开凿出来的绝壁 一直延伸到山顶\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Sheer cliffs soaring to drowned volcanic peaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.50,0:29:43.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,带着海底养分的强大的洋流与海底山相接 便顺山而上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Powerful currents sweep up the mountains' flanks transporting nutrients from deep water towards the summits.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.58,0:29:53.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,坚硬的岩石 给这些绚丽的共生种群提供了很好的停靠地点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The hard rock provides excellent anchorage for communities of great variety and stunning color.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.98,0:29:58.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几米长的软珊瑚\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Soft corals, several meters across
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.78,0:30:03.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,收集流过它们身边的海雪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}collect the marine snow as it drifts past.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.70,0:30:09.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海鞭在海流中伸出手来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Whip corals stretch out into the current.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.70,0:30:16.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大海绵从冰冷的海水中汲取营养\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Giant sponges filter nourishment from the cold water.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.54,0:30:33.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个丰富的物种群落在这里昌盛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A richly varied community flourishes here
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.98,0:30:40.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,得益于洋流持续不断地携带养分从这里流过\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}sustained by the nutrients and detritus in the icy currents that flow around the peak.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.62,0:30:52.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些生物在这座死火山的的繁荣地点, 离阳光照射到的地方还有1英里呢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Yet it is all blossoming on an extinct volcano, a mile below the reach of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.34,0:31:18.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鹦鹉螺\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A nautilus.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.82,0:31:22.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,白天它躲在400米深的海底\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It spends it's days hiding four hundred meters down
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.34,0:31:27.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到了晚上,它就游上来 到珊瑚礁附近寻找食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But as night falls, it ascends up to the reefs, to look for food.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.18,0:31:37.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它那优美的外壳由充满空气的小室组成\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's graceful shell contains gas filled floatation chambers,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.30,0:31:39.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使它可以控制深度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that control it's depth.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.38,0:31:46.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的动力来自虹吸管喷射的水流\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's powered by a jet of water, squirting from a siphon
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.02,0:31:53.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于它是倒着游 所以它自己也很难看清楚自己要去哪里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but it travels shell first, so it can't see exactly where it's going.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.46,0:32:07.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是已经进化到已经没有壳的章鱼和乌贼的近亲\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's nearest living relatives are squid and octopus which, over evolutionary time, have both lost their shells
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.10,0:32:12.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,章鱼也已经成为了猎食鹦鹉螺的主要天敌\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the octopus has become one of the nautilus' major predators.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.98,0:32:15.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,章鱼,伪装的大师\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's a master of disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.82,0:32:24.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鹦鹉螺必须远离它们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The nautilus keeps well clear of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.34,0:32:35.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的小触手有非常灵敏的化学感觉器, 可以探测到敌人和猎物的踪迹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's small tentacles carry highly developed chemical sensors which can detect traces of both predators and prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.82,0:32:45.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鹦鹉螺利用喷水器挖沙子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It uses it's water jet to dig in the sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.02,0:32:56.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它游泳耗费的能量极少, 所以只需每个月吃1顿饭\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Because it devotes so little energy to swimming, it only needs a meal once a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.98,0:33:03.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,得到什么东西了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Got something.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.26,0:33:10.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如愿以偿. 黎明快到了所以它必须回到深海里去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And just as well. Dawn is approaching and it has to puff it's way back, to deeper waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.50,0:33:37.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,30英里外的海上, 大量的鱿鱼游到海面上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Thirty miles away, shoals of squid are jetting upwards towards the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.38,0:33:42.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,晚上,鱿鱼寻找浮游生物和小鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}By night, they seek small fish among the plankton,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.70,0:33:43.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过它们必须谨慎\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but they're cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.94,0:33:54.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太平洋花斑原海豚\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Pacific spotted dolphin.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.22,0:34:00.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们靠声纳导航\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're guided by their sonar.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.42,0:34:09.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海豚经常团队合作\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The dolphin, as so often, are working as a team,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.06,0:34:12.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,协同攻击,来迷惑敌人\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}synchronizing their attacks to confuse their prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.38,0:34:38.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黎明来临, 鱿鱼,鱼和浮游生物再次下沉隐没在黑暗中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As dawn approaches, squid and fish and plankton retreat downwards, to shelter in the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.10,0:35:13.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有一些成为孤岛的火山高耸在海床上达9000米 几乎快要到达海面了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some of these isolated volcanoes rise as much as nine thousand meters from the sea floor, reaching close to the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.46,0:35:21.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里的日照非常充足\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Around these peaks invigorated by daily sunshine
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.14,0:35:25.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海洋中的生物在这里大量繁荣\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}marine life flourishes in spectacular abundance.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.82,0:35:40.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鱼类在这里大量汇聚的原因是 火山迫使洋流把海底的养分送上水面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Fish crowd here, because the volcano forces nutrients to the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.26,0:35:43.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使得浮游生物十分旺盛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}encouraging the plankton to bloom.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.98,0:36:09.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海洋流浪者翻车鱼来到海边让珊瑚鱼给它打扫卫生\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}An oceanic wanderer, a mola mola stops by to be cleaned by reef fish, at the sea mount edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.66,0:36:22.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蝴蝶鱼排成一队忙着吃翻车鱼身上的线体寄生虫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Butterfly-fish pluck string-like parasites from it's flanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.30,0:36:36.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,翻车鱼以超过1000米深的深海水母为生, 那里的水温比这里低20度,\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The huge fish lives on jellyfish over a thousand meters down where the water is twenty degrees colder
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.98,0:36:45.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,翻车鱼可以在下次深海攻击前上来暖和一下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so, a brushup near the surface, allows it to warm up before making more deep water forays.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.34,0:36:58.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个火山已经处于海面之上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The summit of this volcanic mountain rises above the surface of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.14,0:37:02.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阿森松岛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's Ascension Island
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.82,0:37:05.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,距最近的大陆800英里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}eight hundred miles from any other land,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.78,0:37:10.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,长途旅行者们生死攸关的避难所\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a welcome vital haven for long distance travelers.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.14,0:37:19.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,军舰鸟可以在海上持续待几个月\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Frigatebirds spend months continuously airborne at sea
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.98,0:37:24.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过到了筑巢的时候 它就从海洋各处飞回到阿森松岛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but at nesting time, they come to Ascension from all over the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.42,0:37:33.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个充满了火山灰和火山岩的不毛之地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The island's barren slopes of volcanic ash and lava
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.26,0:37:37.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,却提供了一个筑巢的好地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}might seem to offer perfectly good sites for a nest
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.06,0:37:43.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过军舰鸟要挑选偏僻的地点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the frigates choose an even more isolated site
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.26,0:37:50.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水手长鸟岛 阿森松岛旁边的一个偏僻小岛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Boatswain Bird Island, a lonely pillar, just of Ascension's coast.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.02,0:38:03.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阿森松军舰鸟是世界上最轻的海鸟之一 翼展特别长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Frigates are the world's lightest bird, relative to their wingspan
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.66,0:38:07.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们只需要很小的付出就能在海上飞行好几个星期\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they can soar for weeks on end with minimal effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.18,0:38:17.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相对于地上拥挤的巢穴, 在天上飞就悠然自得多了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They seem much more at home in the skies, than in a crowded colony on land
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.38,0:38:19.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过筑巢是必须的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but nest, they must.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.66,0:38:26.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们从大西洋各处飞来,全部聚居在这个岛上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They come from all over the Atlantic to this, their only colony.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.74,0:38:31.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里还有憨鲣鸟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are boobys here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.82,0:38:42.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了生儿育女 全世界的海鸟们才来找这种偏僻的小岛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To raise their young, seabirds worldwide seek such remote islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.54,0:38:56.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水里游的也来这个阿森松岛繁殖\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Swimmers also come to Ascension to breed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.66,0:39:03.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一只雌性绿海龟正在靠近岸边\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A female green turtle approaches the coast.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.30,0:39:08.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它已经有两个月没有吃东西了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She's not eaten once, in two months.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.26,0:39:14.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为她从1000英里外的进食地赶来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She may have traveled one thousand miles from her feeding grounds
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.34,0:39:17.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她的最伟大的旅行\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the greatest journey of her kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.62,0:39:26.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有其他的绿海龟\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Many others are here, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.34,0:39:30.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正在有沙质海床上休憩, 等待黑夜的降临\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}resting on the sandy sea floor awaiting the darkness of night,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.58,0:39:33.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样可以较安全爬上沙滩\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}when it'll be safer to visit the beaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.70,0:39:43.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几周前下的蛋,在这个季节伊始\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Eggs that were laid a few weeks ago, at the start of the season
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.58,0:39:45.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开始孵化了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}are beginning to hatch.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.06,0:40:00.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,多数的蛋是在夜间孵化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Most hatchings happen at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.30,0:40:05.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在是白天,小海龟们很容易受到攻击\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now, in the light of day, the young are extremely vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.86,0:40:14.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们必须尽快爬向大海\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They must get to the sea as soon as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.34,0:40:20.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过小海龟的试炼才刚刚开始\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but their trials have only just begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.42,0:40:37.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,许多小海龟淹死在巨浪中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Many will drown in the pounding waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.58,0:41:03.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在接下来的20年时间里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}During the next twenty years,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.78,0:41:06.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大多数的海龟将不可避免的死去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the vast majority will inevitably die
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.22,0:41:11.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,活下来的海龟最终还会做它们的母亲做过的事情\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but those that survive will, eventually, as their mothers did before them,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.66,0:41:15.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,回到它们孵化过的海滩上繁殖\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}return to the very same beach where they were hatched.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.74,0:41:21.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们如何从1000英里外再次赶回\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}How they find their way back across thousands of miles of open ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.02,0:41:24.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仍然是个谜\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}we still have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.30,0:41:35.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,军舰鸟正在高飞\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A frigate soars.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.90,0:41:42.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水下某个地方一定有食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Somewhere, beneath the surface below, there is the food it must have.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.18,0:41:44.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可在哪里呢?\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But where?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.74,0:41:53.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,飞越海洋的鸟类必须懂得寻找食物的踪迹, 不然就意味着死亡\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Those that fly above the ocean must be able to read the signs of fresh supplies, or perish.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.98,0:41:59.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,距墨西哥海岸100英里,\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A hundred miles from the Mexican coast,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.62,0:42:02.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,军舰鸟锐利的眼睛正在搜寻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and keen eyes have spotted movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.38,0:42:12.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,3米长的旗鱼正在接近猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Sailfish, three meters long, are closing in on prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.42,0:42:22.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们只用恰到好处的力量来猎杀\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They will only use just enough energy to make their kill
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.46,0:42:25.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从不贸然浪费力气\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}never wasting a fin stroke.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.38,0:42:35.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,近100条旗鱼的包围了这群饵鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Nearly a hundred sailfish have surrounded a single school of baitfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.00,0:42:39.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很少能见到上百条的旗鱼在同一个地方出现\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0} It's very rare to see so many of these hunters in one place.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.38,0:42:47.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,旗鱼张开大大的背鳍来把猎物赶到一起\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To herd their prey, the predators raise their huge dorsal fins.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.94,0:43:09.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,旗鱼不恰当的攻击会严重伤害到同伴\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A mistimed strike by one sailfish, could fatally damage another
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.70,0:43:14.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以每条旗鱼不断变换颜色 从蓝色--有斑纹--黑色\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but each continually changes it's color, from blue, to striped, to black
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.90,0:43:20.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这可以警告同伴注意, 同时也可以迷惑饵鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that warns it's companions of it's intentions and also confuses the prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.46,0:43:26.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当饵鱼被赶上海面的时候\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the shoal is driven nearer the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.06,0:43:28.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,又进入了海鸟的攻击范围\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it comes within the range of the seabirds.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.30,0:43:49.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这片空旷的海域中 这些小鱼无处可藏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Out here, in the open ocean, there is nowhere for the baitfish to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.98,0:44:34.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,旗鱼的生活很费能量\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Sailfish live a high obtain life.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.30,0:44:38.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为了生存,它们必须每天寻找猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To survive, they must find prey daily
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.30,0:44:43.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以它们终生都在奔波\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so their entire existence will be spent on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.50,0:45:00.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海洋占据着地球上90%的生存空间\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Over ninety percent on the living space for life on our planet, is in the oceans
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.42,0:45:05.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是现存的最大动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Home to the biggest animal that exists
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.02,0:45:09.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也是史上最大动物的家\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}or has ever existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.86,0:45:11.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蓝鲸\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the blue whale.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.50,0:45:23.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有的重达200吨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some weigh nearly two hundred tons
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.10,0:45:26.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,体积是最大的恐龙的2倍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}twice the size of the largest dinosaur.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.50,0:45:38.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,撇开体积不论, 我们仍然不知道它在这广袤的海洋中去哪里旅行\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Despite their great size, we still have little idea of where they travel in the vast oceans
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.22,0:45:41.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也不知道它们去哪里繁殖\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and none at all of where they go to breed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.02,0:46:15.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这地球上最大的动物只有一种主食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The largest animal on Earth feeds almost exclusively
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.50,0:46:21.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一种非常小的甲壳类动物-磷虾\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}on one of the smallest krill, shrimp-like crustaceans.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.90,0:46:31.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们一口可吃进几吨的海水 然后再过滤出想要的东西\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They take many tons of water into their ballooning throats in a single gulp and sieve out what it contains.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.26,0:46:44.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每天一头蓝鲸可以吃进400万条磷虾\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Every day, each one swallows some four million krill.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.02,0:46:54.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样巨大的食量依赖富饶的海洋的不断提供\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Such gargantuan harvests depend on the continuing fertility of the oceans
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.10,0:47:02.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是全球环境的变化 让蓝鲸赖以生存的浮游生物急剧减少\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But global changes now threaten the great blooms of plankton on which the whales depend.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.42,0:47:08.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,曾经在不久以前\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Once and not so long ago
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.42,0:47:12.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,30万头蓝鲸让海洋看上去充满生气\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}three hundred thousand blue whales roamed the oceans
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.26,0:47:17.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在,只有不足9000头\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}now, less than three percent of that number remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.14,0:47:25.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的星球仍然充满惊奇\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Our planet is still full of wonders.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.90,0:47:32.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当我们探索奇迹的时候 我们所谋取的不仅仅是去了解它,而是征服\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As we explore them, so we gain not only understanding, but power.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.30,0:47:38.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,掌握在我们手里不仅仅是鲸的命运和未来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's not just the future of the whale that today lies in our hands
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.14,0:47:44.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有这个生命星球上所有生命的存亡\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it's the survival of the natural world in all parts of the living planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.34,0:47:50.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要么灭绝它们, 要么关爱它们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}We can now destroy, or we can cherish.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.34,0:47:57.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这取决于人类自己\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The choice is ours.

